*** For those using a Debian-based distribution, such as Ubuntu, there is a ".deb" archive file available: 

user@localmachine$ wget --no-check-certificate --output-document=fizsh_1.0.5-1_all.deb "https://downloads.sourceforge.net/project/fizsh/fizsh_1.0.5-1_all.deb?r=&ts=1294513167&use_mirror=garr" 

The ".deb" archive can be installed by dpkg: 

user@localmachine$ sudo dpkg -i fizsh_1.0.5-1_all.deb 
user@localmachine$ fizsh
Welcome to fizsh, the friendly interactive zshell
Type man fizsh for instructions on how to use fizsh

You are running fizsh version 1.0.5 now.

You may type fizsh-upgrade to upgrade to the latest
version available on the internet.

You may later type fizsh-reinstall to revert to
version 1.0.5 again.

user@localmachine current-directory> 

*** People on RPM-based systems may try: 

user@localmachine$ wget --no-check-certificate --output-document=fizsh-1.0.5-1.noarch.rpm "https://downloads.sourceforge.net/project/fizsh/fizsh-1.0.5-1.noarch.rpm?r=&ts=1294513167&use_mirror=garr" 
user@localmachine$ sudo rpm -Uhv fizsh-1.0.5-1.noarch.rpm
user@localmachine$ fizsh
Welcome to fizsh, the friendly interactive zshell
Type man fizsh for instructions on how to use fizsh
user@localmachine current-directory> 

*** Those on other systems have to use the tarball: 

user@localmachine$ wget --no-check-certificate --output-document=fizsh-1.0.5.tar.gz "https://downloads.sourceforge.net/project/fizsh/fizsh-1.0.5.tar.gz?r=&ts=1294511723&use_mirror=mesh" 

Extract it: 

user@localmachine$ tar -xvzf fizsh-1.0.5.tar.gz 

change directory: 

user@localmachine$ cd fizsh-1.0.5

configure and install: 

user@localmachine$ ./configure && make && sudo make install 

